-- Tom Renney Is Named Coach of NHL's Edmonton Oilers, Replacing Pat Quinn
-- Jay Beberman
-- 2010-06-22T19:21:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/tom-renney-is-named-coach-of-nhl-s-edmonton-oilers-replacing-pat-quinn.html

          
          
             The Edmonton Oilers named Tom Renney
head coach, replacing Pat Quinn.  
 Renney, 55, was coach of the New York Rangers from
2004-2009, compiling a record of 164-117-42.  
 Quinn, 67, will remain with Edmonton in a front-office
position, the National Hockey League team reported on its
website.  
          
          


  


        